                                <condition>Reused in a souterrain, the stone is broken and the beginning of the inscription is missing.</condition>
                            </supportDesc>
                            <layoutDesc>
                                <layout>There is evidence of two inscriptions on the stone. The secondary inscription which is read by Macalister as ...]LL MAQI VORRTIGURN is on two angles of the stone and reads upwards, across the top and then downwards (1945, 93). According to Macalister, there is an older inscription on the stone which <q>was apparently DIOBI - a copy of which has been scratched in minute pin-scrapes on the unoccupied part of the second inscribed angle, perhaps by the representatives of the earlier owner</q> (1945, 93-4).</layout>
                            </layoutDesc>
                        </objectDesc>
                        <handDesc>
                            <handNote>Macalister described the inscription's minute scores as <q>like rather straggling <rs type="execution" key="scratched" ref="https://www.eagle-network.eu/voc/writing/lod/9.html">knife-cuts</rs></q> (1945, 93).
                                <height/>
                            </handNote>
